text: As of 5/7/2020, this location is closed

name: Nem Lawford
text: Update for March 2016 - I decided I would try coming back to this location to see if anything had improved. I was glad to see an entirely new staff of employees. The man at the counter was extremely polite, smiled, and my food was provided …More

name: Monica Diaz
text: we went to order 3 pizzaz and we got 1 pizza wrong. we were the first ones there and then it started filling up, but we were supposed to wait for 7 minutes, and ended up waiting 20 minutes. we waited even more to get the third pizza correct as well. i like the pizza, but its not worth starving to get.

name: Laura Logan
text: When I got home I found that the pizza was only about 30% covered in sauce, I called the store to take the pizza back for a new one. Upon arriving back at the store I spoke with the female manager on duty and proceeded to she her that the …More

name: Lewis Thompson
text: The only good thing about this place is the low price. No drive through. The girl who took my payment (order was called in) looked so depressed she appeared suicidal. …More

name: Kimberly Newby-Dorsey
text: Could of been more prepared for the lunch rush. But overall was great

name: Jim Dice
text: Nice store.  Kind of a pain to get out of the parking lot. Turn right and you have no problem.

name: Savage
text: Awesome food! For $6 a pizza, it's gotta be the best price in town and they always have pizzas ready to go.

name: Travis Lane
text: How is it hot and ready when you always have to wait for it to be cooked. Should give free crazy bread every time you have to wait.

name: Michael Taylor
text: Good customer service, pizza was hot and fresh!

name: Alexander Jepson
text: It's Little Caesars so you get what you pay for, cheap quick pizza. Staff is usually pretty friendly. And this location can go from dead to a line out the door in a few minutes.

name: Adam Sweat
text: Decent pizza, good crazy bread. The best part is the price and the speed

name: Scott Ostrander
text: 3rd one we have gone to tonight, all have been closed with no notice.  I understand renovation but post it to Google and other sites so your customer base is not so inconvenienced

name: Chris Willeford
text: They closed! It's too bad because I liked this branch and they were close to me!

name: forest of too much food the black plague of YouTube
text:
Small location that is really understaffed.
The lay out is more open, but being able to see the prices of the sauces and chilli flakes on the back wall is hard. You have to look at the register. They also didn't have a lot of hot and ready to go pizza and bread ready to go either.

name: Matthew Herman
text: Typical little Caesars: In and out super fast with cheap food. Clean store with friendly staff.

text: Great pizza, quick service!
